524a319a23cB686561e5" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decor=
ation: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000=
000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">own that much sto=
ck</a>. It is not in a heavily regulated industry,=C2=A0and there=E2=80=99s=
 no particular antitrust problem with=C2=A0Musk acquiring it. =E2=80=9CWorl=
d=E2=80=99s richest person acquires the main venue for public communication=
=E2=80=9D does=C2=A0<em>seem=C2=A0</em>like the sort of thing that ought to=
=C2=A0raise regulatory concerns, but in our actually existing system I=E2=
=80=99m not sure what those concerns=C2=A0would be.=C2=A0</p></blockquote><=
p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Again it seems weird to me that the richest per=
son in the world buying the =E2=80=9Ctown square=E2=80=9D (<a href=3D"https=
://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/27381871.266597/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud3=
NqLmNvbS9saXZlY292ZXJhZ2UvZWxvbi1tdXNrLXR3aXR0ZXIvY2FyZC9lbG9uLW11c2stc2F5c=
y1oZS1vZmZlcmVkLXRvLWJ1eS10d2l0dGVyLWJlY2F1c2UtaXQtcy1iZWNvbWUtZGUtZmFjdG8t=
