=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-c=
olor: #ccc;">his words</a>) to privatize it is just fine, while any realist=
ic public-company buyer might run into antitrust trouble, but here we are.=
=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A few other points. First, who would=
 be the CEO of a Musk-owned Twitter? He has indicated that he wants to repl=
ace current management. He has=C2=A0a number of other full-time jobs himsel=
f, so is probably not available. But he clearly wants=C2=A0to meddle. What =
a terrible job running Twitter for him would be. A few levels down, who is =
going to run Twitter=E2=80=99s anti-abuse, trust and safety etc. functions,=
 when Musk has made it clear he <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusin=
ess.com/click/27381871.266597/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud3NqLmNvbS9hcnRpY2xlcy9lbG9uL=
